    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Binary Literals</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Body Text">Binary literals are written as 0h12345678abcdef</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text">The value behind 0h is a sequence of hex numbers. Each pair of hex numbers (nibble) represents 1 byte. There must be an even number of &apos;nibbles&apos;.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text">The compiler compiles these literals into a byte[] array which is stored into a variable of the type <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="BINARY">BINARY</link></para>
  </body>
